<Issue id="13256" key="FAB-925" number="925" project="10002" reporter="jimthematrix" assignee="jimthematrix" creator="jimthematrix" type="10003" summary="Improve coding styles in headless-tests.js for chaining Promise-based APIs" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2016-11-02 01:53:43.0" updated="2018-07-20 14:10:40.0" resolutiondate="2016-11-03 02:46:22.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="36596"> <description><! CDATA the current headless-tests.js have a lot of embedded promise-based calls, like below:  functionA() .then( function(result) { // do stuff functionB() .then( function(result) {...}); });  this is defeating the purpose of the design of Promise-based APIs, it should have been chained like below (note the "return" statement on the call to functionB()):  functionA() .then( function(result) { // do stuff return functionB(); }) .then( function(result) {...}); );   ></description> </Issue>
